text: A police officer in Fairfax County, Virginia, faces up to three years in prison in connection with his arrest and use of a stun gun on a black man who cried out, "I can't breathe." https://t.co/dcgS3o6tQG

text: DC Mayor Muriel Bowser said Sunday she believes the federal law enforcement response to protests after the police killing of George Floyd encouraged more people to participate and do so peacefully. https://t.co/NiHvG2eo2g
